<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-04T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3160d</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the State</gloss>
                                to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-04T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>814. The Department has received reports which indicate that American
                            prisoners in Germany will not be given same treatment as prisoners of
                            other countries but will be confined with negroes and given degrading
                            treatment. Request Spanish Government to ascertain whether these reports
                            are well founded and, if so, upon what grounds the German Government
                            intends to adopt the attitude indicated.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>